Author: Katie Delaney

AUGUSTA, Maine — As temperatures drop, public safety officials are encouraging people to make sure they're heating their homes safely.

This time of year, the [state fire marshal’s office](https://www.maine.gov/dps/fmo/) sees a rise in fires sparked by various heating sources. Last month, there was a massive [house fire in Falmouth](/video/news/local/public-safety/space-heater-may-have-caused-falmouth-house-fire/97-7dded9e9-123d-4e5d-bad4-f9133d573971) that investigators said appears to have been started by a space heater.

